40|$|An intense <b>terahertz</b> (THz) <b>radiation</b> {{generated}} by the beating of two Langmuir waves, which are excited by the forward Raman scattering, is analyzed theoretically. The radiation energy per shot can {{be as high as}} 0. 1 J, with the duration of 10 pico-second. Appropriate plasma density and the laser characteristics are examined...|$|R
